explanation:
Rationale for each symbol (concise):

- OS_ObjectIdGetById
  Required because OS_DirectoryRewind directly calls it. To decide MISRA for-loop compliance you must inspect its implementation for any for-loops (their loop counters, side effects, or use of objects modified by called functions).

- OS_DirRewind_Impl
  Required because OS_DirectoryRewind directly calls it. Its body may contain for-loops or call other functions that do; those loops must be inspected against the rule.

- OS_ObjectIdTransactionInit
  Included because it is a direct callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById (per the call graph). Any for-loops in it (or objects it modifies) are part of the behaviour of functions called from OS_DirectoryRewind and must be examined.

- OS_ObjectIdToArrayIndex
  Included because it is called by OS_ObjectIdGetById. It likely manipulates object/index tables and could contain for-loops or modify objects used as loop counters; inspect for compliance.

- OS_ObjectIdConvertToken
  Included because it is called by OS_ObjectIdGetById. It may perform iterations or modify tokens/indices that interact with loops higher up; needed to determine if any for-loop uses objects modified in called functions.

- OS_ObjectIdTransactionCancel
  Included because it is called by OS_ObjectIdGetById. It may contain loops or modify shared objects/flags used elsewhere; include in analysis.

- OS_ObjectIndexFromToken
  Included because it is called by OS_DirRewind_Impl. It may perform indexing logic with loops; inspect for loop-counter usage and side effects.

- osal_id_t
  Type of dir_id parameter passed into OS_ObjectIdGetById. Needed to determine whether this identifier or related objects could be used as loop counters or flags in called functions.

- OS_object_token_t
  Type of token used to hold the resolved object. Required to see whether the token contains fields that might be used/modified as loop counters or flags inside called functions.

- int32
  Return type used by OS_DirectoryRewind and called functions; include to interpret return codes and control flow (e.g. early returns that might avoid loops).

- OS_SUCCESS
  Constant tested after OS_ObjectIdGetById. Required to understand the control flow (whether OS_DirRewind_Impl is invoked) and thus whether any for-loops in the callee(s) are exercised.

- OS_LOCK_MODE_NONE
  Constant passed into OS_ObjectIdGetById. Included because it might alter internal control paths (and conditional loops) in OS_ObjectIdGetById.

- LOCAL_OBJID_TYPE
  Constant passed into OS_ObjectIdGetById. As above, it can affect which code paths/loops are executed inside OS_ObjectIdGetById.

Notes:
- The UT_* test/stub symbols shown in the call graph are not invoked by the target source lines and are not necessary unless the implementation of the above functions dispatches to them; inspect the listed functions first.
- Also, if any of the listed functions reference additional global object tables or helper functions that contain for-loops (e.g., object table arrays, iterator helpers), those symbols must be added to the analysis once discovered. The above list is the minimal set deduced from the static call graph and the target function source.
